data: Birds lay eggs to reproduce.  Eggs are delicious
A horse is a mammal.  Mammals are warm-blooded animals that have fur or hair.  They give birth to live young.
Platypus are mammals that lay eggs.  They are very strange mammals.
Eagles are large birds of prey with excellent eyesight. They lay eggs in high nests.
Kangaroos are marsupials. They carry their young in pouches and give birth to live offspring.
Crocodiles are reptiles that lay eggs in nests near water. They are cold-blooded and have scaly skin.
Salmon are fish that migrate upstream to lay eggs in freshwater rivers.
Frogs lay eggs in water. Their eggs hatch into tadpoles before becoming adult frogs.
Penguins are flightless birds that lay eggs and raise their chicks on icy terrain.
Elephants are the largest land mammals. They give birth to live young after long gestation periods.
Ducks lay eggs in nests near water. Their ducklings are born able to swim almost immediately.
Lizards are reptiles that can regrow their tails and usually lay soft-shelled eggs.
Some sharks lay eggs, while others give birth to live young. Their reproduction is diverse.
Ostriches are the largest birds. They lay the biggest eggs of any living land animal.
Bats are the only mammals capable of sustained flight. They give birth to live young.
Turtles lay their eggs in holes dug into the sand. Hatchlings must crawl to the sea.
Newts are amphibians that undergo metamorphosis from larvae to adults and lay eggs in water.
Hummingbirds lay tiny eggs and build cup-shaped nests often hidden under leaves.
Whales are marine mammals. They give birth to live calves and nurse them underwater.
In seahorses, the male carries the eggs in a pouch until they hatch.
Giraffes give birth standing up. Their calves fall several feet to the ground at birth.
Toads lay eggs in long gelatinous strings in shallow water.
Falcons are birds of prey known for their speed. They lay eggs in cliffside nests.
Humpback whales are known for their complex songs. These marine mammals use sound to communicate.
